                    James has led accounts and projects with diverse clients in industry, education, government, and civil society, on projects such as:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Led a design system team</strong> that helped a financial institution realize its efficiency and quality goals.</li>
                    <li><strong>Built and governed a design system</strong> to achieve brand cohesiveness across dozens of vendor and in-house teams with over a hundred native apps.</li>
                    <li><strong>Facilitated c-suite ideation</strong> toward an app's MVP, then led the team to realize the concept via prototypes. </li>
                    <li><strong>Led the research and design team</strong> to overhaul the federal government's assistance for victims of identity theft.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    James designed navigation schemes for several of the world's largest companies and organizations. He relishes thorny information architecture problems, leveraging years of experience and a Master’s Degree in Library/Information Science from the University of Maryland. 
